This paper is about cross-media retrieval, which involves multiple types of media such as image and text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which focuses on the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also proposes a deep learning approach, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses domain adaptation and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
